tp://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=235.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~nsmessageboard/ezboard/posticons/1.gif" align=absmiddle>  Suggestions for new categories.</span><hr size=1> Please post any ideas right here straight off the top of your head as you think of them. Just keep it clean. I have already considered and junked the notion of an adult forum. It might have boosted activity past Pluto but would also have closed us down. How about a space babe category. Post a picture of your favourite space girl. It can be film, anime, perhaps a real astronaut lass even, we can be flexible on this. <br>Inventors forum? So many people have ideas for a space drive. A category dedicated to posting your own and then having it savaged by our semi regular science buffs. I know a couple of threads which could be transplanted there. <br>Space sport? Wrestling in zero G? Suggestions for sports in space such as solar sailing. Once around the sun. The winner isnt the one to finish first. The winner is the one who survives the trip without expiring from old age. The trophy may not be handed out.<br>Submersible racing at Europa? Moon buggy challenges. Rock climbing on Mars. Tennis on Titan. Golf on Ganymede. Radiation level permitting. Lunar basketball. Who says white men cant jump! <br><br>Comeon. Somebody has to have better suggestions than those.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/utmayes1999.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tmayes1999</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NEP Freighter Crewman</span><br>  Posts: 99<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(5/8/02 11:46:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=235.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~nsmessageboard/ezboard/posticons/1.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Suggestions for new categories.</span><hr size=1> 1. Add a forum to discuss space flight related physics, mathematics, science, and engineering.<br><br>2. Add a forum to design, and discuss specific designs  for robotic, and crewed space vehicles.<br><br>3. Add a a form to discuss possible  space weapons, and warfare of the future.<br><br>4. Add a forum for the design, and discussion of credible<br>plans  for robotic, and crewed starships. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uprojectorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 1120<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(5/9/02 3:49:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=235.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~nsmessageboard/ezboard/posticons/1.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Suggestions for new categories.</span><hr size=1> Some good ideas. I was already planning a war and terrorism section.  I think more technical forums are a good idea. Also an asteroid watch.<br><br>I simply dont want to have too many forums at the moment. What I may do is merge the less active forums and then math, physics, engineering and general science forum for discussion of space vehicles and starships. If it gets enough traffic we can split it into more specialised topics. First I'll merge those topics which are too similar.<br><br>Its going to take awhile. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=x>X</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NEP Freighter Crewman</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(5/9/02 9:54:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=235.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~nsmessageboard/ezboard/posticons/Bart-term.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Suggestions for new categories.</span><hr size=1> What about a section where we can organize activities that we could do on our own.  One idea: what about we do experiments of our own in high-powered rocketry or mixing lunar simulant to make concrete.  I heard NASA gives the stuff away.  Oh, if you don't what lunar simulant is, it's material mixed together to resemble the soil on the moon.  I can't stand waiting on NASA to do anything.  In fact, I'm tempted to do what that little kid did and make our own breeder reactor.  Come on, if we pull our resources together, maybe we can finally get somewhere. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uprojectorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 1123<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(5/10/02 5:03:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=235.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~nsmessageboard/ezboard/posticons/3.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Suggestions for new categories.</span><hr size=1> A mad scientist forum then? I like that. Quite a few threads could be transplanted immediately. We can post &quot;how to's&quot; on breeder reactors, atomic weaponry and life support systems used in submarines etc. Anything useful for an atomic or space project. A picture of Jimmy Neutron at the top of the category might be suitable. <br><br>We post there until Uncle Sam comes around and breaks our fingers. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uprojectorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 1139<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(5/13/02 9:05:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=235.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~nsmessageboard/ezboard/posticons/1.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Suggestions for new categories.</span><hr size=1> I intend to remove 'regulations' and merge 'media' and 'politics' into, well, 'Media and Politics'.  I will try to shorten the number of categories by moving threads into broader base ones but haven't made a move yet. I think this would be better since we have a lot of categories. Here's what I'm thinking of adding. What do you think?<br><br><br>War<br>Space weapons, future conflict, atomic arsenals, nuclear terrorism, unrest........<br><br>Engineering<br>Math, science, physics, design, mechanical, aeronautics, robotics, environment.......<br><br>Mad Scientists<br>Projects to try at home, projects not to try at home........<br><br>A glitch is preventing me from making category changes but I can still move threads around. If the glitch clears up I will start work. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/ujohnfraz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>John Fraz</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://members.hometown.aol.com/_ht_a/naturyl/images/YinYangsblack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NEP Freighter Crewman</span><br>  Posts: 88<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(5/15/02 12:54:22 pm)</font><br>   